<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-428-125  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 428 125.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  July 24 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Moscow: program to translate computer docs to Russian announced.andO;(by PROMT cybernetic system)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Tchashchin, Kirill.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Product DevelopmentSoftware packagesRussian languageMS-DOSLanguage Translation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MOSCOW: PROGRAM TO TRANSLATE COMPUTER DOCS TO RUSSIAN ANNOUNCED MOSCOW,U.S.S.R., 1990 JUL 11 (NB) -- A Leningrad-based team of programmers andlanguage scientists has developed an MS-DOS program to translatecomputer-related materials from English to Russian.andM;The program called PROMT, presented at the recent PC World Forum, is acomplex cybernetic system using a linguistic database.andP;  It contains a moderndictionary of about 25,000 words and advanced grammar.andP;  The system softwareensures not only an integrated environment for the translation process butalso the maintenance of a database and special tools for linguisticinvestigations.andM;The version for translating text from English requires 7Mb of hard drivespace and 575 KB (kilobytes) of computer memory.andP;  A price for the program hasnot yet been determined.andP;  Versions for translating texts from French, Italianand other languages will be available this fall.andM;The program is very fast and translates computer-related texts with a 98percent accuracy rate.andM;The developers are currently in the dealer selection process.andP;  They expect tohave a dealer network and start shipping PROMT early this fall.andM;(Kirill Tchashchin/19900713)</TEXT></DOC>